Angular is an open source Javascript framework used to create web apps

Angular was created by google and is supported by a large community 

To Install Angular 
npm install -g @angular/cli
ng new name-app // name of the project
cd name-app
ng serve //Builds and serves your app

Update Angular
ng update @angular/cli @angular/core

There are built in features such as:
- routing
- style sheets

Prerequiste to install angular:
- Nodejs( An open-source, cross-platform, JavaScript runtime environment that executes JavaScript code outside a web browser.)
- Npm (a package manager for the JavaScript programming language)
- Angular CLI
- IDE

Folder Structure
e2e - end to end testing is used for integration testing and helps ensure the application works fine.
node_modules - show available packages within the project
src - where the code is :) 
angular.json - project name and version of the cli
package.json - tells which files to be install in node_modules
tsconfig.json - the compiler options required during compilation
tslint.json - the config file with rules to be considered while compiling


